body:
The following code errors, but if I replace `b`'s type with e.g. `u32`, I do not get any error. Additionally `foo` is dropped after `bar`. Moderately confusing that the error is about `Foo: Drop` and not `Foo::b: Drop`.

```rust
#[derive(Debug)]
struct Foo {
    a: u32,
    b: String,
}

impl Drop for Foo {
    fn drop(&mut self) {
        println!("drop {:?}", self);
    }
}

fn main() {
    let foo = Foo { a: 5, b: String::new() };
    let bar = Foo { a: 42, ..foo };
}

```

([Playground](https://play.rust-lang.org/?version=stable&mode=debug&edition=2015&gist=c17c1973d8cfa4cd05af89631963b895))

Errors:

